class krrood.ormatic.wrapped_table.ColumnConstructor#

Represents a column constructor that can be used to create a column in SQLAlchemy.

name: str#

The name of the column.

type: str#

The type of the column. Needs to be like “Mapped[<type>]”.

constructor: typing_extensions.Optional[str] = None#

The constructor call for sqlalchemy of the column.

class krrood.ormatic.wrapped_table.AssociationTable#

Represents an association table for many-to-many relationships in SQLAlchemy.

name: str#

The name of the association table.

left_table_name: str#

The name of the left (source) table.

left_foreign_key: str#

The foreign key column name for the left table.

left_primary_key: str#

The full primary key reference for the left table (e.g., ‘TableName.primary_key’).

right_table_name: str#

The name of the right (target) table.

right_foreign_key: str#

The foreign key column name for the right table.

right_primary_key: str#

The full primary key reference for the right table (e.g., ‘TableName.primary_key’).

class krrood.ormatic.wrapped_table.WrappedTable#

A class that wraps a dataclass and contains all the information needed to create a SQLAlchemy table from it.

wrapped_clazz: krrood.class_diagrams.class_diagram.WrappedClass#

The wrapped class that this table wraps.

ormatic: krrood.ormatic.ormatic.ORMatic#

Reference to the ORMatic instance that created this WrappedTable.

builtin_columns: typing_extensions.List[ColumnConstructor] = []#

List of columns that can be directly mapped using builtin types

custom_columns: typing_extensions.List[ColumnConstructor] = []#

List for custom columns that need to by fully qualified as triple of (name, type, constructor)

foreign_keys: typing_extensions.List[ColumnConstructor] = []#

List of columns that represent foreign keys as triple of (name, type, constructor)

relationships: typing_extensions.List[ColumnConstructor] = []#

List of relationships that should be added to the table.

mapper_args: typing_extensions.Dict[str, str]#
primary_key_name: str = 'database_id'#

The name of the primary key column.

polymorphic_on_name: str = 'polymorphic_type'#

The name of the column that will be used to identify polymorphic identities if any present.

skip_fields: typing_extensions.List[krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField] = []#

A list of fields that should be skipped when processing the dataclass.

property primary_key#
property child_tables: typing_extensions.List[WrappedTable]#
property has_children: bool#

Indicate whether this table has subclasses in the generated DAO model.

The check is performed in two simple steps: - Use the inheritance graph to determine direct children of this wrapped class. - Additionally, scan existing wrapped tables for any table that resolves this

instance as its parent_table (covers alternative-mapping hierarchies).

create_mapper_args()#
property full_primary_key_name#
property tablename#
property parent_table: typing_extensions.Optional[WrappedTable]#

Resolve the parent DAO table for this table.

This first tries to use a direct inheritance relation. If that is not available and this table is an alternative mapping, it resolves the parent through the original classes’ inheritance and maps back to the correct DAO table.

Returns:

The parent WrappedTable or None if there is no parent.

property is_alternatively_mapped#
property fields: typing_extensions.List[krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField]#
Returns:

The list of fields specified only in this associated dataclass that should be mapped.

parse_fields()#
parse_field(wrapped_field: krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField)#

Parses a given WrappedField and determines its type or relationship to create the appropriate column or define relationships in an ORM context. The method processes several types of fields, such as type types, built-in types, enumerations, one-to-one relationships, custom types, JSON containers, and one-to-many relationships.

This creates the right information in the right place in the table definition to be read later by the jinja template.

Parameters:

wrapped_field – An instance of WrappedField that contains metadata about the field such as its data type, whether it represents a built-in or user-defined type, or if it has specific ORM container properties.

create_builtin_column(wrapped_field: krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField)#

Creates a built-in column mapping for the given wrapped field. Depending on the properties of the wrapped_field, this function determines whether it’s an enum, a built-in type, or requires additional imports. It then constructs appropriate column definitions and adds them to the respective list of database mappings.

Parameters:

wrapped_field – The WrappedField instance representing the field to create a built-in column for.

create_type_type_column(wrapped_field: krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField)#

Create a column for a field of type Type. :param wrapped_field: The field to extract type information from. :return:

get_table_of_wrapped_field(wrapped_field: krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField) → WrappedTable#
Parameters:

wrapped_field – The wrapped field to get the table for.

Returns:

The wrapped table for the given wrapped field.

create_one_to_one_relationship(wrapped_field: krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField)#

Create a one-to-one relationship with using the given field. This adds a foreign key and a relationship to this table.

Parameters:

wrapped_field – The field to get the information from.

create_one_to_many_relationship(wrapped_field: krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField)#

Creates a many-to-many relationship mapping for the given wrapped field using an association table. This allows multiple instances of the source table to reference the same instances of the target table.

Parameters:

wrapped_field – The field for the many-to-many relationship.

create_json_column(wrapped_field: krrood.class_diagrams.wrapped_field.WrappedField)#

Create a column for a list-like of built-in values.

Parameters:

wrapped_field – The field to extract the information from.
